# EcoMetric Frontend Engineering Standards

Senior frontend bar: intentional, polished, production-ready. Never AI-looking slop.

## Before Writing Code

1. Inspect existing project structure, conventions, components, tokens, naming.
2. Follow existing conventions over this rule when they conflict.
3. If repo is empty (greenfield): scaffold first (see Greenfield Bootstrap).
4. If Figma is available: read frame hierarchy, auto layout, typography, spacing, tokens before coding.
5. Understand workflow: primary data, empty/error/loading states, responsive behavior.

## Tech Stack

- React 19, TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS + CSS variables + design tokens, mobile-first
- shadcn/ui, Radix UI, Lucide React
- React Router v7
- TanStack Query (server read state), useMutation (writes/auth)
- Zustand (cross-route client state only: session, preferences)
- React Hook Form + Zod
- clsx, class-variance-authority, tailwind-merge (`cn` utility)
- Framer Motion only when it improves usability feedback

## Greenfield Bootstrap

If no codebase exists:

1. `pnpm create vite . --template react-ts`
2. Install: `pnpm add` tailwindcss, @tailwindcss/vite, react-router, @tanstack/react-query, zustand, react-hook-form, @hookform/resolvers, zod, clsx, tailwind-merge, class-variance-authority, lucide-react
3. Init shadcn/ui (`components.json`, path alias `@/`)
4. Create `src/` architecture (below)
5. Define tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css` + Tailwind theme
6. Then implement the requested feature

## Project Architecture

```
src/
  app/           # providers, router, query client
  assets/
  layouts/
  shared/        # cross-feature only
  features/      # feature-owned code
  styles/
```

Per feature when needed:

```
features/<name>/
  api/ components/ hooks/ pages/ schemas/
  services/ store/ types/ utils/ index.ts
```

Rules:
- No random folders; no feature code in `shared/`
- Named exports; strict types; no `any`
- Presentation components never fetch API directly
- Prefer composition over configuration

## State Tooling

| Tool | Use when |
|------|----------|
| TanStack Query | Server-fetched lists, detail, dashboards |
| useMutation | Login, register, CRUD, form submit |
| useState | Local UI (toggle, open/close) |
| Zustand | Auth session, global UI prefs across routes |
| Do NOT add | Query/Zustand on screens with no server/global state |

## Output Tiers

**Tier A â€” Feature screen** (Dashboard, Data Input):
page, components, api, hooks, schemas, loading/empty/error/success

**Tier B â€” Auth screen** (Login, Register):
page, form components, schema, mutation hook, submitting/error/success

**Tier C â€” Shared primitive** (Button, Badge):
component + variants + types only

## Design Token Priority

1. Map Figma values â†’ `src/styles/tokens.css` and Tailwind theme
2. Components use semantic classes: `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`
3. No raw hex in components
4. Arbitrary Tailwind values only when token missing â€” then add the token immediately
5. No inline styles

### EcoMetric Brand (from Figma ecometrix)

- Font: Inter
- `--primary`: #006d36 | `--foreground`: #00150c | `--muted-foreground`: #414844
- `--border`: #c1c8c2 | `--accent`: #4ade80 | `--background`: #f7f9fb
- Input/button height: 48px (h-12)
- Radius: 8px inputs/buttons, 12px cards, 24px glass preview card
- Icons: prefer Lucide equivalents of Figma vectors

## Screen Types

**App screens** (dashboard, tables, operational forms):
enterprise-dense, content-first, scannable, no marketing fluff

**Auth/public screens** (login, register, landing):
follow Figma split layouts, hero copy, decorative previews; allow marketing type scale (e.g. 48px H1 in auth panel)

## UI Anti-Patterns (avoid)

- Purple everywhere, huge gradients, rounded-2xl everywhere
- Giant cards, generic heroes, shadow overload
- Decorative UI without workflow purpose
- Desktop-first layout
- Spinner-only loading for primary content
- Hardcoded colors, arbitrary spacing without token mapping

## UI Patterns (use)

- Clean enterprise dashboard aesthetics
- Professional spacing via Tailwind scale: p-4, gap-3, px-6
- Skeletons for content loading; empty states with actions; error with retry
- Semantic HTML before ARIA; WCAG AA contrast
- Keyboard: Tab, Enter, Escape, Space; visible focus rings
- Every input has label; every icon button has aria-label
- Responsive: 320, 768, 1024, 1440px â€” mobile-first, no horizontal overflow

## Forms

React Hook Form + Zod. Handle: defaults, validation errors, server errors, submitting, success.
Accessible labels and helpful error messages.

## Figma Rules

When Figma MCP available:
- Read components, frames, auto layout, spacing, typography before coding
- Reuse tokens; match design system
- Login frame: `71:6252` | Register: `74:8070` | File key: `BzmfxP0dmTwmf72pb7U7Mv`
- No Figma Variables in file â€” tokens are inferred from design context

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Path alias: `@/` â†’ `src/`

## Final Checklist

Before finishing:
- [ ] Responsive 320/768/1024/1440
- [ ] Keyboard accessible, WCAG AA
- [ ] Loading, empty, error, success where relevant
- [ ] Feature-based folders; shared only when reusable
- [ ] No `any`, no duplicated code, no inline styles
